sentence: US stocks were slightly higher in late trading as economic data and testimony from Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell failed to provide a lot of direction for investors Tuesday.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average, S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite Index were indicated to close slightly higher in a choppy session that saw the widely watched gauges spend some time underwater.
The Dow was held back by losses in Caterpillar ( CAT ) and Home Depot ( HD ), which posted results that fell short of Wall Street expectations.
